snippet.textDisplay: The translation of "Be-parwaah" here as "un-caring" is a bit mis-leading....  I think Shah Hussain is using this word synonymous as "Be-Niaz"referring to the God whose existence is "independent" of other creation....... Also in the stanza "across the river is my Ranjha.......... i made a pledge and must go to him......... i beg the boatman to take me there", hes using the following metaphors .......River: metaphor for materalistic life, Ranjha metaphor for God,  boatman metaphor for Angel of death...........

snippet.textDisplay: I don't get why people expect season 8 to be exactly like seasons 1-6. The point of Coke Studio is to showcase all Pakistani talent, which is not just confined to Qawwali and Rohail Hayat. Even Rohail featured younger artists, New Age music, and other genres. Those videos just weren't as popular. Strings have done a great job bringing their own flair to this season and have contributed so much to the Pakistani music scene in general.
snippet.textOriginal: I don't get why people expect season 8 to be exactly like seasons 1-6. The point of Coke Studio is to showcase all Pakistani talent, which is not just confined to Qawwali and Rohail Hayat. Even Rohail featured younger artists, New Age music, and other genres. Those videos just weren't as popular. Strings have done a great job bringing their own flair to this season and have contributed so much to the Pakistani music scene in general.
